race.comment: WORLD'S MY OYSTER (3) was an emphatic winner when resuming, putting away Florey, who has since bolted in against CIELAO, which franked the form nicely. With natural improvement second-up, she looks a talented type on the rise. THE SPRINKLER (5) has been right on the cusp in both runs back, just lacking the knockout punch late. He's peaking now and sticks with Toeroek, so a breakthrough wouldn't shock. CIELAO (7) is flying and continues to give bold on-pace showings. She'll try to pinch it again, though she's unlikely to get things entirely her own way this time. ZARKANA (9) will relish a strong tempo and be launching late, he just can't afford to be spotting them too big a start. HEADPHONES (4) is another who'll be strongest through the line. She loves this trip and is doing enough to be considered.
